    <header>
        <h1>Seasonal Water Changes</h1>
        <p>Adapting to the Rhythms of Nature</p>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="season-section">
            <h2>Spring</h2>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Spring+Water" alt="Spring Water">
            <p>Spring brings warmer temperatures and increased rainfall, leading to higher water levels in many areas.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Increased snowmelt can cause flooding in some regions.</li>
                <li>Agricultural runoff may increase nutrient levels in water bodies.</li>
                <li>Prepare for potential changes in water quality and availability.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="season-section">
            <h2>Summer</h2>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Summer+Water" alt="Summer Water">
            <p>Summer's high temperatures can lead to increased evaporation and lower water levels, especially in drier climates.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Water conservation becomes crucial during this season.</li>
                <li>Increased demand for water for irrigation and recreation.</li>
                <li>Algae blooms may occur due to warmer water and higher nutrient levels.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="season-section">
            <h2>Autumn (Fall)</h2>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Autumn+Water" alt="Autumn Water">
            <p>Autumn often brings cooler temperatures and increased rainfall in some areas, replenishing water supplies.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Reduced evaporation rates help restore water levels.</li>
                <li>Leaf litter can impact water quality in streams and rivers.</li>
                <li>Prepare for potential storms and changes in water runoff.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="season-section">
            <h2>Winter</h2>
            <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/400x200?text=Winter+Water" alt="Winter Water">
            <p>Winter brings colder temperatures and potential snowfall, which can significantly affect water availability.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Frozen water bodies can impact aquatic life.</li>
                <li>Snowpack accumulation is crucial for water supply in many regions.</li>
                <li>Prepare for potential ice jams and flooding during thaws.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

